problem_prompt:
Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in literature would. What is the SMILES expression of N-formyl-N-methylcyclopropanecarboxamide?
Answer:
gpt_response: The SMILES (Simplified Molecular Input Line Entry System) expression of N-formyl-N-methylcyclopropanecarboxamide can be written as CC1(C1)C(=O)NC=O. This notation represents the molecular structure of the compound in a condensed format, capturing the connectivity of the atoms and bonds without explicitly displaying the three-dimensional geometry. It is a widely used system in computational chemistry and chemical informatics for representing chemical structures in a concise and standardized manner.
